{"title_page": "Henrique Sereno", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2013}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Henrique Sereno\n| image = Sereno-2.jpg\n| image_size = 200\n| caption = Sereno as a [[Real Valladolid|Valladolid]] player in 2010\n| fullname = Henrique Sereno Fonseca<ref name=Profile>{{cite web|url=https://maisfutebol.iol.pt/sereno/fc-porto/1574-399-18083|title=Sereno|publisher=Mais Futebol|language=Portuguese|accessdate=11 April 2020}}</ref>\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1985|5|18|df=y}}<ref name=Profile/>\n| birth_place = [[Elvas]], Portugal<ref name=Profile/>\n| height = {{height|m=1.88}}<ref name=Profile/>\n| position = [[Defender (association football)#Centre-back|Centre back]]\n| currentclub =\n| clubnumber =\n| youthyears1 = 1995\u20132004\n| youthclubs1 = Os Elvenses\n| years1 = 2004\u20132005\n| years2 = 2005\u20132010\n| years3 = 2006\n| years4 = 2010\n| years5 = 2010\u20132013\n| years6 = 2011\u20132012\n| years7 = 2012\u20132013\n| years8 = 2013\u20132015\n| years9 = 2015\u20132016\n| years10 = 2016\n| years11 = 2017\n| years12 = 2017\n| clubs1 = [[O Elvas C.A.D.|O Elvas]]\n| clubs2 = [[Vit\u00f3ria S.C.|Vit\u00f3ria Guimar\u00e3es]]\n| clubs3 = \u2192 [[F.C. Famalic\u00e3o|Famalic\u00e3o]] (loan)\n| clubs4 = [[Real Valladolid|Valladolid]]\n| clubs5 = [[FC Porto|Porto]]\n| clubs6 = \u2192 [[1. FC K\u00f6ln]] (loan)\n| clubs7 = \u2192 [[Real Valladolid|Valladolid]] (loan)\n| clubs8 = [[Kayserispor]]\n| clubs9 = [[1. FSV Mainz 05|Mainz 05]]\n| clubs10 = [[ATK (football club)|ATK]]\n| clubs11 = [[UD Almer\u00eda|Almer\u00eda]]\n| clubs12 = [[Chennaiyin FC|Chennaiyin]]\n| caps1 = 25\n| caps2 = 54\n| caps3 = 23\n| caps4 = 12\n| caps5 = 7\n| caps6 = 25\n| caps7 = 20\n| caps8 = 41\n| caps9 = 0\n| caps10 = 10\n| caps11 = 1\n| caps12 = 18\n| totalcaps = 236\n| goals1 = 1\n| goals2 = 2\n| goals3 = 0\n| goals4 = 0\n| goals5 = 0\n| goals6 = 0\n| goals7 = 1\n| goals8 = 4\n| goals9 = 0\n| goals10 = 1\n| goals11 = 0\n| goals12 = 1\n| totalgoals = 10\n| nationalyears1 = 2007\n| nationalyears2 = 2013\n| nationalteam1 = [[Portugal national under-21 football team|Portugal U21]]\n| nationalteam2 = [[Portugal national football team|Portugal]]\n| nationalcaps1 = 1\n| nationalcaps2 = 2\n| nationalgoals1 = 0\n| nationalgoals2 = 0\n| club-update =\n| nationalteam-update =\n}}\n\n'''Henrique Sereno Fonseca''' (born 18 May 1985), known as '''Sereno''', is a Portuguese former professional [[Association football|footballer]] who played as a [[Defender (association football)#Centre-back|central defender]].\n\n==Club career==\n===Guimar\u00e3es===\nBorn in [[Elvas]], [[Alto Alentejo Subregion|Alto Alentejo]], Sereno joined [[Vit\u00f3ria S.C.|Vit\u00f3ria de Guimar\u00e3es]] for [[2005\u201306 Primeira Liga|2005\u201306]] from hometown's [[O Elvas C.A.D.|O Elvas CAD]], and served a loan stint during the latter part of that season at lowly [[F.C. Famalic\u00e3o]].\n\nIn the [[2007\u201308 Primeira Liga|2007\u201308 campaign]] he, alongside Brazilian [[Pedro Geromel]], formed a solid defensive partnership as Vit\u00f3ria came from the [[Segunda Liga|second division]] into a final third [[Primeira Liga]] position. On 9 March 2008 he scored a rare goal, in a 2\u20130 home win against [[Sporting CP]].<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.uefa.com/memberassociations/news/newsid=670176.html | title = Guimar\u00e3es defeat Sporting to go third | publisher = UEFA | date = 9 March 2008 | accessdate = 28 December 2011}}</ref>\n\nSereno spent the vast majority of [[2008\u201309 Primeira Liga|2008\u201309]] in the sidelines after having undergone surgery to both knees, only appearing in six games.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.guimaraesdigital.com/noticias/37133/sereno-foi-operado-com-sucesso-aos-dois-joelhos|title=Sereno foi operado com sucesso aos dois joelhos|trans-title=Sereno had successful surgery to both knees|publisher=Guimar\u00e3es Digital|language=pt|date=21 October 2008|accessdate=3 October 2017}}</ref> After beginning the following season again in the starting XI (nine matches, one goal), he eventually terminated his contract and, on 1 February 2010, signed with [[Real Valladolid]] in Spain for five months.<ref>{{cite news | url = http://www.marca.com/2010/02/01/futbol/equipos/valladolid/1265048513.html | title = El Valladolid ficha al central portugu\u00e9s Henrique Sereno |trans-title=Valladolid sign Portuguese centre-back Henrique Sereno | newspaper = [[Marca (newspaper)|Marca]] | language = es | date = 1 February 2010 | accessdate = 28 December 2011}}</ref>\n\nSereno made his debut for his new team on 20 March 2010, playing the entire 2\u20130 away victory over [[Deportivo de La Coru\u00f1a]].<ref>{{cite news | url = http://www.eldiadecordoba.es/deportes/Primera-victoria-Valladolid_0_352464892.html | title = Primera victoria en 2010 del Valladolid |trans-title=First 2010 win for Valladolid | newspaper = El D\u00eda de C\u00f3rdoba | language = es | date = 21 March 2010 | accessdate = 9 August 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Porto===\nIn late June 2010, after [[2009\u201310 La Liga|Valladolid's relegation]] in [[La Liga]], Sereno returned to his country, signing with [[FC Porto]] on a [[Free transfer (association football)|free transfer]].<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.maisfutebol.iol.pt/fcporto/sereno-fc-porto-porto-valladolid/1168469-1304.html | title = F.C. Porto: Sereno confirmado como refor\u00e7o por quatro \u00e9pocas | trans-title = F.C. Porto: Sereno confirmed for four seasons | publisher = Mais Futebol | language = pt | date = 8 June 2010 | accessdate = 11 October 2012 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20140329101034/http://www.maisfutebol.iol.pt/fcporto/sereno-fc-porto-porto-valladolid/1168469-1304.html | archive-date = 29 March 2014 | url-status = dead }}</ref> On 20 August 2011, deemed surplus to requirements as practically all Portuguese players, he joined German club [[1. FC K\u00f6ln]] on a [[2011\u201312 Bundesliga|season]]-long loan deal.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.fc-koeln.de/news/detailansicht/?tx_ttnews%5Btt_news%5D=3758&cHash=509d1add7410f7681715c5f699a80e2e | title = Henrique Sereno verst\u00e4rkt den FC |trans-title=Henrique Sereno strengthens FC | publisher = FC K\u00f6ln | language = de | date = 20 August 2011 | accessdate = 11 October 2012}}</ref>\n\nSereno made his [[Bundesliga]] debut on 27 August 2011, playing the full 90 minutes in a 4\u20133 away defeat of [[Hamburger SV]].<ref>{{cite web | url = http://espnfc.com/uk/en/report/321011/report.html?soccernet=true&cc=5739 | title = Late goals hand Cologne dramatic win | publisher = [[ESPN FC|ESPN Soccernet]] | date = 27 August 2011 | accessdate = 11 October 2012}}</ref> He featured regularly during the campaign, but his team suffered relegation.\n\nSereno returned to Valladolid and Spain's top flight for the [[2012\u201313 La Liga|2012\u201313 season]], still under contract with Porto.<ref>{{cite news | url = http://realvalladolid.elnortedecastilla.es/noticias/2012-08-22/sereno-vuelve-blanquivioleta-201208222250.html | title = Sereno vuelve a ser blanquivioleta | trans-title = Sereno again a ''blanquivioleta'' | newspaper = [[El Norte de Castilla]] | language = es | date = 22 August 2012 | accessdate = 11 October 2012}}</ref> He scored his only goal for the former on 24 February 2013, in the 2\u20131 away win against [[Rayo Vallecano]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.levante-emv.com/deportes/2013/02/24/valladolid-congela-ideas-rayo-vallecano/977067.html|title=El Valladolid congela las ideas del Rayo Vallecano|trans-title=Valladolid freeze Rayo Vallecano's ideas|newspaper=[[Levante-EMV]]|language=es|date=24 February 2013|accessdate=11 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Later years===\nIn summer 2013, Sereno joined [[Kayserispor]] from Turkey. He made his [[S\u00fcper Lig]] debut on 15 September, featuring the full 90 minutes in a 1\u20131 draw at [[Gen\u00e7lerbirli\u011fi S.K.|Gen\u00e7lerbirli\u011fi SK]]; he ended [[2013\u201314 S\u00fcper Lig|the campaign]] with 22 matches and three goals, in an eventual relegation as last.\n\nOn 27 July 2015, [[free agent]] Sereno returned to Germany by penning a two-year deal with [[1. FSV Mainz 05]].<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.bundesliga.de/de/liga/news/mainz-verpflichtet-henrique-sereno-1-fsv-mainz-05.jsp | title = Mainz verpflichtet Henrique Sereno |trans-title=Mainz acquire Henrique Sereno | publisher = [[Bundesliga]] | language = de | date = 27 July 2015 | accessdate = 3 August 2016}}</ref> The following 15 June, however, after no competitive appearances, he was released.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.goal.com/de/news/968/transfernews/2016/06/15/24654792/mainz-l\u00f6st-vertrag-mit-henrique-sereno-auf | title = Mainz l\u00f6st Vertrag mit Henrique Sereno auf |trans-title=Mainz cancel Henrique Sereno's contract | publisher = [[Goal (website)|Goal]] | language = de | date = 15 June 2016 | accessdate = 3 August 2016}}</ref>\n\nSereno scored his first goal for his next club, [[ATK (football club)|Atl\u00e9tico de Kolkata]], on 18 December 2016. It proved to be the equaliser as they went on to win [[2016 Indian Super League Final|the final]] of the [[Indian Super League]] on [[Penalty shoot-out (association football)|penalties]], against [[Kerala Blasters FC]].<ref name=ISL>{{cite news | url = http://www.hindustantimes.com/football/atletico-de-kolkata-crowned-isl-2016-champions-after-beating-kerala-blasters-fc/story-9WrkSZzrU73zJnH3LYobQN.html | title = Atletico de Kolkata crowned ISL 2016 champions after beating Kerala Blasters FC | newspaper = [[Hindustan Times]] | first = Dhiman | last = Sarkar | date = 18 December 2016 | accessdate = 20 December 2016}}</ref>\n\nOn 31 January 2017, Sereno signed a six-month contract with [[Segunda Divisi\u00f3n]] side [[UD Almer\u00eda]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.udalmeriasad.com/noticia/el-central-henrique-sereno-se-convierte-en-el-tercer-refuerzo-invernal|title=El central Henrique Sereno se convierte en el tercer refuerzo invernal|trans-title=Stopper Henrique Sereno becomes the third winter signing|publisher=UD Almer\u00eda|language=es|date=31 January 2017|accessdate=1 February 2017}}</ref> On 15 September he returned to the Indian top tier, joining [[Chennaiyin FC]] for free<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/football/indian-super-league-chennaiyin-fc-sign-mailson-alves-and-henrique-sereno/story-qhq76DkgKs5nfX1PuIrxWO.html|title=Indian Super League: Chennaiyin FC sign Mailson Alves and Henrique Sereno|newspaper=Hindustan Times|date=15 September 2017|accessdate=12 October 2017}}</ref> and going on to act as [[Captain (association football)|captain]] for the eventual champions.<ref name=ISL2>{{cite web|url=https://scroll.in/field/943509/how-john-gregorys-chennaiyin-went-from-isl-champions-to-strugglers-in-the-space-of-two-seasons|title=How John Gregory\u2019s Chennaiyin went from ISL champions to strugglers in the space of two seasons|publisher=[[Scroll.in]]|first=Kaushal|last=Shukla|date=13 November 2019|accessdate=11 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nTwo years after announcing his retirement at the age of 34, Sereno became president of [[U.D. Vilafranquense]], with the Portuguese second tier club overcome by severe financial problems.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.publico.pt/2020/03/30/desporto/noticia/henrique-sereno-vai-rombo-dificil-1909943|title=Henrique Sereno: \u201cVai ser um rombo, mas o mais dif\u00edcil est\u00e1 feito\u201d|trans-title=Henrique Sereno: \u201cIt will be a big loss, but the hardest part is done\u201d|newspaper=[[P\u00fablico (Portugal)|P\u00fablico]]|first=Augusto|last=Bernardino|language=pt|date=30 March 2020|accessdate=3 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\nSereno made his debut for [[Portugal national football team|Portugal]] on 10 June 2013, playing the second half of a 1\u20130 [[Exhibition game|friendly]] win with [[Croatia national football team|Croatia]] in Geneva.<ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.uefa.com/european-qualifiers/news/020a-0e1411a5fba1-7b161d3051d8-1000--portugal-win-the-day-as-halilovic-enters-fray/ | title = Portugal win the day as Halilovi\u0107 enters fray | publisher = UEFA  | first = Elvir | last = Islamovi\u0107 | date = 10 June 2013 | accessdate = 11 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nOn 24 June 2016, the Elvas city hall commended Sereno for his sporting achievements.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.radioportalegre.pt/index.php/8-radio/5723-camara-de-elvas-aprova-voto-de-louvor-ao-futebolista-henrique-sereno.html | title = C\u00e2mara de Elvas aprova voto de louvor ao futebolista Henrique Sereno |trans-title=Elvas city hall approves commendation of footballer Henrique Sereno | publisher = R\u00e1dio Portalegre | language = pt | date = 24 June 2016 | accessdate = 3 August 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n===Club===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Club\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Season\n!colspan=\"3\"|League\n!colspan=\"2\"|Cup\n!colspan=\"2\"|Other\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n|-\n!Division!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|[[O Elvas C.A.D.|O Elvas]] \n|[[2004\u201305 Terceira Divis\u00e3o|2004\u201305]]<ref name=FJ>{{cite web|url=https://www.foradejogo.net/player.php?player=198505180001&language=2|title=Sereno|publisher=ForaDeJogo|accessdate=24 December 2017}}</ref>\n|[[Portuguese Third Division]]\n|25||1||0||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||25||1\n|-\n|rowspan=\"5\"|[[Vit\u00f3ria S.C.|Vit\u00f3ria Guimar\u00e3es]]\n|[[2006\u201307 Liga de Honra|2006\u201307]]<ref name=FJ/>\n|[[Segunda Liga]]\n|12||0||0||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||12||0\n|-\n|[[2007\u201308 Primeira Liga|2007\u201308]]<ref name=FJ/>\n|[[Primeira Liga]]\n|27||1||4||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||31||1\n|-\n|[[2008\u201309 Primeira Liga|2008\u201309]]<ref name=FJ/>\n|Primeira Liga\n|6||0||0||0||0||0||6||0\n|-\n|[[2009\u201310 Primeira Liga|2009\u201310]]<ref name=FJ/>\n|Primeira Liga\n|9||1||6||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||15||1\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n!54!!2!!10!!0!!0!!