o-fascist Greek party takes third place in wave of voter fury|date=21 September 2015|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/sep/21/neo-fascist-greek-party-election-golden-dawn-third-place}}</ref><br />[[Social conservatism]]<ref>{{cite book|page=196|title=Crisis, Movement, Strategy: The Greek Experience|publisher=BRILL|first=Panagiotis|last=Sotiris|year=2018}}</ref><br />[[National conservatism]]<ref>{{cite book|page=47|title=Aligning Geopolitics, Humanitarian Action and Geography in Times of Conflict|first=Gerry|last=O'Reilly|year=2019|publisher=Springer}}</ref><br />[[Economic nationalism]]<ref>{{cite journal|title=Thirties Throwbacks: Explaining the Electoral Breakthroughs of Jobbik and Golden Dawn|year=2014|publisher=[[Tufts University]]|first=William|last=Rose|url=http://as.tufts.edu/politicalscience/sites/all/themes/asbase/assets/documents/research/thirtiesThrowbacks.pdf}}</ref><br />[[Euroscepticism|Hard Euroscepticism]]<ref name=\"euroscrepticism5\">[https://eu.boell.org/sites/default/files/greek_right_wing_populist_parties_and_euroscepticism.pdf Antonis Galanopoulos: Greek right-wing populist parties and Euroscepticism](PDF), p.2 \"Golden Dawn is also Eurosceptical and it is opposing Greece's participation in the European Union and the Eurozone\"</ref><ref name=\"euroscrepticism6\">[http://www.france24.com/en/20140527-europe-pictures-european-parliament-eurosceptic-parties-fn-ukip France24: A look at the European Parliament's eurosceptic parties], Golden Dawn, Greece</ref><ref name=\"euroscrepticism7\">[https://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/sep/16/greek-election-2015-golden-dawn-austerity The Guardian: Greek election 2015: Golden Dawn rises on austerity-driven despair], \"In successive opinion surveys, the virulently [...] anti-EU party has emerged as Greece's third-biggest political force\"</ref><ref name=\"euroscrepticism8\">[http://www.ft.com/cms/s/2/783e39b4-e4af-11e3-9b2b-00144feabdc0.html#slide0 Financial Times: Anti-EU parties celebrate election success], 26 May 2014</ref><br />[[Right-wing populism]]<ref>{{cite journal|first=Mats|last=Ekstr\u00f6m|title=Right-wing populism and the dynamics of style: a discourse-analytic perspective on mediated political performances|journal=Palgrave Communications|date=3 July 2018|volume=4|issue=83}}</ref><br />[[Anti-globalization|Anti-globalism]]<ref name=\"anti-globalization9\">[https://www.independent.co.uk/voices/commentators/the-golden-dawn-a-love-of-power-and-a-hatred-of-difference-on-the-rise-in-the-cradle-of-democracy-8210724.html Independent: The Golden Dawn: A love of power and a hatred of difference on the rise in the cradle of democracy], \"The economic ethos of European neo-fascism, from the Golden Dawn to the British National Party, has historically been anti-neoliberal and anti-globalization\", 14 October 2012</ref><br />[[Anti-communism]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.902.gr/eidisi/voyli/77523/hydaios-antikommoynismos-apo-ti-nazistiki-hrysi-aygi-sti-voyli|title=\u03a7\u03c5\u03b4\u03b1\u03af\u03bf\u03c2 \u03b1\u03bd\u03c4\u03b9\u03ba\u03bf\u03bc\u03bc\u03bf\u03c5\u03bd\u03b9\u03c3\u03bc\u03cc\u03c2 \u03b1\u03c0\u03cc \u03c4\u03b7 \u03bd\u03b1\u03b6\u03b9\u03c3\u03c4\u03b9\u03ba\u03ae \u03a7\u03c1\u03c5\u03c3\u03ae \u0391\u03c5\u03b3\u03ae \u03c3\u03c4\u03b7 \u0392\u03bf\u03c5\u03bb\u03ae \u2013 902.gr|accessdate=15 August 2017|date=15 October 2015}}</ref><br />[[Islamophobia]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://cik.leeds.ac.uk/2017/10/25/traversing-ideological-boundaries-islamophobia-in-greece/|title=Traversing ideological boundaries: Islamophobia in Greece : Counter-Islamophobia Kit|website=cik.leeds.ac.uk}}</ref><br />[[Antisemitism]]<ref>https://gr.boell.org/en/2017/08/01/antisemitism-greece-today-executive-summary</ref><ref>https://www.haaretz.com/jewish/how-anti-semitic-is-greece-really-1.5248999</ref><br />[[Anti-Turkism]]<ref>http://www.hurriyetdailynews.com/neo-nazi-golden-dawn-says-istanbul-will-be-greek-22118</ref><br />[[Anti-immigration]]<ref name=\" 